a";s:88:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 02 Mar 2016 10:52:20 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2390";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:536:"<p>This one has been a long time in the making but we''re super excited to launch it. Crafthouse is a WooCommerce Furniture Theme designed for the contemporary furniture company looking for a fresh and modern look for their website.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/">Our First Theme of 2016 is Live, Say Hello to Crafthouse a WooCommerce Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2469:"<p><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/crafthouse-woocommerce-furniture-theme/14542098?ref=obox">Crafthouse</a> has been a project that we&#8217;ve been busy with since December of 2015. A furniture theme designed by an incredibly talented South African, <a href="http://www.ianroblambert.com/">Ian Lambert</a>, we wanted something that fits perfectly into Layers&#8217; ability to create different layouts with the click of a button.</p>\n<p>When Ian presented us with the initial designs we were so happy that we jumped directly into the conversion phase. The result is what you see here, a WooCommerce theme aimed at modern furniture companies who are looking for a fresh look for their website.</p>\n<p><a href="http://themeforest.net/item/crafthouse-woocommerce-furniture-theme/full_screen_preview/14542098?ref=obox" target="_blank" rel="attachment wp-att-2391"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2391" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots.jpg" alt="crafthouse-screenshots" width="1000" height="339" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots-300x102.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots-768x260.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/crafthouse-screenshots.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></a></p>\n<p>We love it and know you will too with it&#8217;s minimal look, sharp typography and inspiring demo content.</p>\n<p>As with any Layers theme created by our team, we have made sure it works seamlessly with all our plugins and has been tested with all the options available in the free version of Layers. Dynamic header layouts, multiple widgets and the 100&#8217;s of different Content Widget combos have been factored into it&#8217;s design.</p>\n<p>Crafthouse can be bought on Themeforest for $46 and comes packaged with <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/storekit/">StoreKit</a> absolutely free. <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/crafthouse-woocommerce-furniture-theme/full_screen_preview/14542098?ref=obox">Check out the demo</a> and let us know what you think in the comments!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/">Our First Theme of 2016 is Live, Say Hello to Crafthouse a WooCommerce Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/03/our-first-theme-of-2016-is-live-say-hello-to-crafthouse/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"Linking just got a lot easier with Layers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 18 Feb 2016 07:52:50 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Uncategorized";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2231";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:356:"<p>We just dropped a new version of Layers which includes an improved linking interface and the death of FOUC.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/">Linking just got a lot easier with Layers</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2335:"<h3>What the FOUC happened?</h3>\n<p>Flash Of Unstyled Content, which up till now has been a bit of a bugbear with Layers, is no longer an issue. With the release of Layers 1.2.12 we have made some major changes to the way custom CSS is loaded and the result is a much smoother and modern experience for first time visitors to your site.</p>\n<p>No longer will they see a flash of a grey unstyled site, but instead a perfectly format destination just as you designed it. Releasing a fix for this has been something we&#8217;ve been trying to do for a while and are really happy to have it out there now!</p>\n<h3>Linking just got overhauled</h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dynamic-linking-1212.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2242"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2242" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/dynamic-linking-1212.png" alt="dynamic-linking-1212" width="660" height="760" /></a></p>\n<p>Another new feature in Layers 1.2.12 is a brand new linking interface in our content and slider widgets. This massive update makes it much easier (and more dynamic) to link between pages and posts within your site.</p>\n<p>The interface will now allow you to choose between an outbound link or dynamic content within your website. The benefits are huge:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Changing links within your site no longer requires that you go to each Layers page and update hard coded URL&#8217;s.</li>\n<li>By relying on WordPress&#8217; core linking architecture your permalink settings will now automatically apply to the buttons in your sliders and content widget.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Finally, you can now also determine whether or not a link opens in a new window. Happy Days <img src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<p>Be sure to update your version of Layers today and get hold of two awesome new features which continue to make Layers the most user friendly <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/">WordPress Site Builder</a> in the World.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/">Linking just got a lot easier with Layers</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/linking-just-got-a-lot-easier-with-layers/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"6";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here’s Why You Should Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 04 Feb 2016 13:59:46 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"layers updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2182";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:467:"<p>The latest version of Layers is now live with a brand new Page Revisions feature that will give you piece of mind the next time you make any change to one of your Layers pages.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/">Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here&#8217;s Why You Should Update</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4684:"<h3>Introducing Page Revisions</h3>\n<p>Having piece of mind while you make changes to your site is important. There is nothing worse than accidentally deleting something you cannot recover and until today that was a scary possibility. We have been so focused on page revisions that we decided to release it before any other new 2016 features (more on that in a moment).</p>\n<p>So what do Page Revisions do? Well now every time you save a page, we will automatically store that as a version that you can revert back to at any point in the future. That means you can make as many changes as you like and should you not like them, you can roll back to a previous version with relative ease.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2193"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2193" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png" alt="revisions-02" width="1683" height="880" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-300x157.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-768x402.png 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02-1024x535.png 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/revisions-02.png 1683w" sizes="(max-width: 1683px) 100vw, 1683px" /></a></p>\n<p>In order to roll back all you need to do is go to the &#8220;Edit Page&#8221; section in WordPress, click on the specific page you want to revert and then click on &#8220;Revisions&#8221;. In there you&#8217;ll be presented with a timeline slider that will allow you to easily go back to a different state.</p>\n<p>The knock on affect of this change is equally important as we&#8217;re now storing your content in the same place that SEO plugins look. So from now on, Yoast, All in One SEO etc. are 100% compatible with Layers. It&#8217;s a big deal and one we&#8217;re quite proud of.</p>\n<h4>Some other important changes</h4>\n<p>Along with Page Revisions there have been some other changes on the admin site which you may find important:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>We&#8217;ve split out our admin CSS file into three separate files for easier management across different interfaces.</li>\n<li>The marketplace section has had a <em>complete redesign</em>, making it easier to browse and preview items.</li>\n<li>You can now select a primary color during the onboarding process. No more grey websites!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>So don&#8217;t waste any time and update to Layers 1.2.11 directly from your WordPress dashboard</p>\n<h4>What&#8217;s Next?</h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2190"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2190" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png" alt="new-link-interface-01" width="660" height="710" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1-279x300.png 279w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/new-link-interface-01-1.png 660w" sizes="(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px" /></a></p>\n<p>With version 1.2.11 live we are already fully focused on the next release, here&#8217;s what you can look forward to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Smart/Dynamic linking &#8211; no more hard coding of page links! This will make it much easier to transfer a site from a dev environment to a live environment.</li>\n<li>Better onboarding &#8211; making Layers easier for new users is a pillar of the product so onboarding will be looked at in Feb.</li>\n<li>New preset page layouts &#8211; we want to expand our preset page layout options.</li>\n<li>New grid system &#8211; this isn&#8217;t guaranteed for the next release but is a huge focus for me (David) as we aim to make our grid layout more flexible.</li>\n<li>New HTML for SEO friendliness &#8211; this was planned for 1.2.11, but has been pushed out.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>One last thing!</h3>\n<p>February marks one year since Layers was <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/02/from-today-the-way-you-build-wordpress-sites-will-change-say-hello-to-layers/">launched to the world</a>. Keep an eye out for our &#8216;bundle-a-week&#8217; special via our new newsletter called&#8230; &#8220;<a href="http://us10.campaign-archive1.com/?u=5b9a020fcf797987098cc7bca&amp;id=e7874277f7">Not another Newsletter</a>&#8221; which is sent every week!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/">Layers 1.2.11 Has Just Dropped, Here&#8217;s Why You Should Update</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/02/layers-1-2-11-has-just-dropped-heres-why-you-should-update/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"What’s In Store For Layers in early 2016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 05 Jan 2016 13:09:11 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"layers updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2147";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:394:"<p>The new year is already well underway at Layers HQ as we ramp up for an exciting 2016 with a packed development schedule focused on the Layers core.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/">What&#8217;s In Store For Layers in early 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3845:"<p>We had such an overwhelmingly positive response to <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> in the few short months it has been growing, and have several crazy-cool ideas for how to make it even more perfect. However, we know the furniture still gets wet if there is a hole in the roof and we want to ensure Layers is the best it can be, always. That&#8217;s why it will be receiving our full attention in the first quarter of 2016. Below is a peek at some of the things we will be looking at in-depth:</p>\n<h3>Onboarding</h3>\n<p>User friendliness is Layers primary feature. When you jump in for the first time, our setup wizard helps you along with basic configurations and video examples of using the customizer. Interface improvements, updated content and a variety of beautiful new presets are on the way to spice up the Layers Dashboard and onboarding process to delight you right into your next website project.</p>\n<h3>SEO</h3>\n<p>WordPress is already built to be extremely effective at SEO without much more effort than turning on permalinks, but when it comes to pages on your site, you&#8217;re at a disadvantage. Google already tends to rank your internal content higher when building search engine results due to its denser keywords &#8211; ignoring dynamic pages created from templates as those pages themselves actually contain no content and duplicate information from other pages on your site. This can make home page optimization tough!</p>\n<p>SEO is a top development priority for us in the coming months, and will include an overhaul of the HTML structure in the theme templates to ensure the HTML5 outline of your pages is optimal and up to 2016 standards.</p>\n<h3>Page Revisions</h3>\n<div id="attachment_2152" style="width: 1000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2152"><img class="wp-image-2152 size-full" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png" alt="history-alpha" width="990" height="374" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha-300x113.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha-768x290.png 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/history-alpha.png 990w" sizes="(max-width: 990px) 100vw, 990px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Alpha version of our new page history feature</p></div>\n<p>Using the revisions API you&#8217;ll soon be able to roll back to a previous version of your page should you not be happy with your changes or if your server experiences any unwanted issues. The aim here is piece of mind <img src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>\n<h3>Performance</h3>\n<p>WordPress 4.4 <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/" target="_blank">introduced big improvements</a> to the Customizer in both use and performance, but with every big change always comes a little gremlin to make something else act out. We will be going in with flamethrowers in the coming weeks to flush out these annoyances and make the Layers customization experience smoother than ever before.</p>\n<p>Have Something You Want In Layers Not Listed Here?</p>\n<p>We love hearing from you on how you are using Layers and what features you would like to see and welcome you to submit feature requests on our <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/forums/" target="_blank">Layers Community site.</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/">What&#8217;s In Store For Layers in early 2016</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"http://www.layerswp.com/2016/01/whats-in-store-for-layers-in-2016/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:109:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 10 Dec 2015 20:26:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"layers pro";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2107";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:421:"<p>Overall the response to Layers Pro has been incredible so we wanted to keep the momentum and make it even better.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/">Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"David Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6834:"<h3>Let&#8217;s start with Layers Pro</h3>\n<p>Overall the response to Layers Pro has been incredible so we wanted to keep the momentum and make it even better.</p>\n<p>So with a big focus on serving you, our most valued users, we are happy to announce some big improvements:</p>\n<h4><strong>Background Videos</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/background-video.gif" rel="attachment wp-att-2119"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2119" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/background-video.gif" alt="background-video" width="640" height="300" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally Background videos are a possibility in Layers, allowing you to make bold visual statements when users enter your site.</p>\n<h4><strong>Social Widget</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png" rel="attachment wp-att-2118"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2118" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png" alt="social-icons-widget" width="1100" height="314" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-300x86.png 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-768x219.png 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1-1024x292.png 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/social-icons-widget-1.png 1100w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p>This widget took much longer to developer than expected but it was for good reason. Our focus on UX is obsessive and we refused to release our Social Icon Widget until it was as intuitive as possible. We believe we have achieved that with global link inputs, widget and menu selection as well as the normal settings you&#8217;ve come to expect from Layers &#8211; including button coloring and sizing.</p>\n<h4><strong>Search in the Header</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2113"><img class="size-full wp-image-2113 aligncenter" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg" alt="search-pop-up" width="1100" height="790" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-300x215.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-768x552.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-1024x735.jpg 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up-1000x720.jpg 1000w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/search-pop-up.jpg 1100w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p>With Layers Pro you can now add a search button to the header of your site using a simple checkbox. When turned on, a search icon will appear inline with your menu and reveals a beautifully animated popup interface to search in.</p>\n<h4><strong>Header Background Image</strong></h4>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2111"><img class="size-full wp-image-2111 aligncenter" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg" alt="header-background" width="1100" height="488" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-300x133.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-768x341.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background-1024x454.jpg 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-background.jpg 1100w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p>Layers Pro introduced deeper header customization and to make that even better we’re introducing header background image uploading.</p>\n<p>Last but not least we&#8217;ve added a <strong>Body Color Selector</strong> and improved <strong>Menu Styling</strong> which included hover states!</p>\n<p>If you don’t have Layers Pro yet, <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/layers-pro-extended-customization-for-layers/11225042?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Layers%20Pro%201.2">get it now for $25</a></p>\n<h3><b>StoreKit Updates</b></h3>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2112"><img class="size-full wp-image-2112 aligncenter" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg" alt="header-cart-drop-down" width="1100" height="600" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-300x164.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-768x419.jpg 768w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down-1024x559.jpg 1024w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/header-cart-drop-down.jpg 1100w" sizes="(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/storekit-woocommerce-for-layers/11223808?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20StoreKit%201.6">StoreKit</a> has served as the backbone to the most valuable ecommerce functionality available for Layers. This week we’ve launched an update which adds a Header Mini Cart as well as new filters to the product widget including the ability to show only items on sale or only featured items.</p>\n<h3><b>Two new themes</b></h3>\n<p>If that wasn’t enough we also focused on getting two new themes out the gates before the end of 2015. They’re called Acquire 2.0 and Concept Living…</p>\n<p>Concept Living, announced a few weeks ago, is part of a strategy to bring some of our best selling themes onto the Layers platform &#8211; find out more about the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living">Furniture theme</a> here.</p>\n<p>Acquire 2.0 is a big update of one of the first ever Layers themes. We decided to give it a more comprehensive design along with more page templates to choose from. Check out the demo or go directly to the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/acquire-wordpress-corporate-theme/11220959?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Layers%20Blog%3A%20Acquire%202.0">business theme</a> to find out more.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/">Ending 2015 With Big Updates to Layers Pro, StoreKit and Two Of Our Themes</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:105:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/background-videos-social-widget-menu-customization-and-so-much-more/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"5";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"What’s in Layers 1.2.10";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 08 Dec 2015 14:49:49 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"development";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2083";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:504:"<p>You ask, we listen.  Layers 1.2.10 out and includes several fixes and code improvements to make the new WordPress 4.4 update even better. We also have a ton of Layers improvements coming your way for the holidays, plus some huge additions to our Extensions that are sure to make you smile.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/">What&#8217;s in Layers 1.2.10</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3148:"<p>Before jumping into updating Layers, be sure to update your Layers Updater plugin to version 1.2. You can find this updated version under Layers &gt; Dashboard. See <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/update-layers/" target="_blank">this doc for or step-by-step instructions on updating your plugin</a>.</p>\n<h3>Fixed Transparent Headers Are Back</h3>\n<p>We made several changes in 1.2.8 to where options are placed in the Customizer to make finding them easier. One of these changes included a slick little toggle for the Sticky Header that basically hid the Transparency option unless you turned Sticky on. We realize now that was confusing for some people, so these two options are no longer dependent on one another.</p>\n<p>Layers Pro users who have access to the Blog customizer will also find their sidebar layout options inside the related Posts &amp; Pages section rather than up under Site Settings.</p>\n<h3>Video Backgrounds</h3>\n<p>A few years ago, when we first introduced video backgrounds into our Obox Slider, we had no idea how popular it would really be. Video use in web design was just beginning to trend and we weren&#8217;t sure if the average person would have any idea how to take advantage of them.</p>\n<p>Since then video backgrounds have exploded across the web and proved a big success in terms of added functionality. We felt Layers needed this in the core, too, and so the Layers Slider Widget will now support embedded video from Vimeo, YouTube or a self-hosted .mp4 when the <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> extension is active. This feature, along with several more goodies, are coming later this week with Layers Pro 1.2, so keep an eye on this space or <a href="https://twitter.com/Oboxthemes" target="_blank">our Twitter feed</a> for the announcement.</p>\n<p>For designers, this means you no longer need to resort to using a different slider plugin to get full motion graphics into your slider. For developers, this means even better controls for adding your own options to the core widgets to expand their functionality in your own themes and extensions.</p>\n<h3>Bug Fixes</h3>\n<p>Layers 1.2.10 fixes several niggles, including a missing round image ratio in the Posts widget, Boxed slider alignment issues, and a missing content container in archives with no content. We naturally aim to have Layers be 100% bug free one day, but to make that happen we need your help.</p>\n<p>To get help with Layers issues or report a possible bug, and to contribute your ideas and code to the project, be sure to visit our <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com" target="_blank">Community Forums</a> and <a href="https://github.com/Obox/layerswp" target="_blank">GitHub project</a>.</p>\n<p>To learn more about the technical additions to this update, or for help with updating, visit the <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/layers-release-1-2-10/" target="_blank">1.2.10 update page</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/">What&#8217;s in Layers 1.2.10</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/12/whats-layers-1-2-10/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"Get Excited for Faster Layers Customization in WordPress 4.4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 30 Nov 2015 15:26:50 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2054";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:483:"<p>WordPress 4.4 is due for release on December 8th, bringing a host of front-end improvements and developer love. See what goodies are in store for Layers and how this is the best WordPress update yet!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/">Get Excited for Faster Layers Customization in WordPress 4.4</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4673:"<p>WordPress 4.4 is due for release on December 8th (hopefully there are no delays like last time), bringing a host of front-end improvements and developer love. We are especially excited for this release as it means even more improvements to Customizer performance and responsive image handling.</p>\n<p>Version 4.4 also means the full implementation of the REST API, making it even easier to include common libraries like Ajax in your plugins. For more on that specifically, see the <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/10/28/rest-api-welcome-the-infrastructure-to-core/" target="_blank">introductory post over on Make WordPress Core</a>.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at the most exciting improvements coming in this release:</p>\n<h4>Performance Improvements</h4>\n<p>As <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/10/what-the-new-wordpress-customizer-roadmap-means-for-layers/" target="_blank">previously reported</a>, WordPress 4.4 promises the first of the Customizer Roadmap for improving performance and functionality of site customization. How this translates to you and your Layers site is that<span class="s1"> widgets are no longer all loaded at once, creating a massive performance slump as the Customizer interface is loaded.</span></p>\n<p><span class="s1">Instead, each Widget gets initialized only when it is needed.  This leads to a more snappy interface when changing and updating your widgets in the Customizer, and a far quicker initial load of the interface.</span></p>\n<h4>Responsive Images</h4>\n<p>As of today, the average web page <a href="http://httparchive.org/interesting.php?a=All&amp;l=Sep%2015%202015#bytesperpage">currently weighs over 2 MB</a> with the majority of those bytes being attributed to images. Rapidly evolving browser, screen size and resolution support across mobile devices also means site owners are having to include more and more image versions, sizes or formats.</p>\n<p>WordPress saw the opportunity to make a huge impact on the web &#8211; seeing as how it runs more than 25% of all websites &#8211; by adding responsive image support out of the box so sites can serve appropriate sizes images to all users.</p>\n<p>If you are a child theme developer, you can take advantage of these changes through wp_get_attachment_image_srcset and the srcset attribute in the image tag. An example of the implementation can be found on the WordPress <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/09/30/responsive-images-merge-proposal/" target="_blank">developer blog</a>.</p>\n<h4>Your Content is Now Embeddable</h4>\n<p>WordPress has allowed you to easily embed content from oEmbed providers such as YouTube and SoundCloud by adding share links to your post content or widgets, and with 4.4 your WordPress site is now its own <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/10/28/new-embeds-feature-in-wordpress-4-4/" target="_blank">oEmbed provider</a>! This means others can embed your content the same way and have it automatically appear in a neat oEmbed format.</p>\n<p>Using a handful of filters, you can customize how your site looks when it’s embedded elsewhere. As a part of the work around embeds, there are also a couple of new functions for retrieving and displaying embeddable content. The post above also links to a <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/disable-embeds/">plugin</a> which will remove the ability to embed your site elsewhere.</p>\n<h4>Updating WordPress</h4>\n<p>If you develop child themes or extensions, or just want to check out the new 4.4 features before it hits on the 8th,  you can grab the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-beta-tester/">WordPress beta Tester</a> plugin to easily sync to the latest build. Of course, we don&#8217;t recommend you install WordPress 4.4 on a live website before it is actually released.</p>\n<p>You should begin seeing the update notifications hit your WordPress admin, beginning next Tuesday, with a possible week delay if you have a Managed WordPress solution that updates it for you.</p>\n<p>For more information about WordPress 4.4 and an overview of the REST API and other developer goodies, head over to the <a href="https://make.wordpress.org/core/2015/11/11/wordpress-4-4-field-guide/">WordPress 4.4 Field Guide</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>What are you looking forward to in future versions of WordPress? Let us know in the comments below.</strong></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/">Get Excited for Faster Layers Customization in WordPress 4.4</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/get-excited-for-wordpress-4-4-faster-layers-customization/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:46:"Easy WordPress White-labeling For Your Clients";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 24 Oct 2015 12:46:10 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Tips";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"brand wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"white label";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=1775";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:471:"<p>We discuss all the ways you can white-label your client site through things as simple as turning off the Layers link in the footer, to which plugins allow for the easiest logo replacement and admin customization.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/">Easy WordPress White-labeling For Your Clients</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Vail Joy";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12618:"<p>If you design or setup websites for clients, you know how important it is to offer a smooth and branded, yet client-proof administration experience. White-labeling is a term that describes re-branding or removing 3rd party branding from your website&#8217;s front and back-end. Doing so increases brand recognition for your design company or service.</p>\n<p>While it is not possible to completely re-brand a WordPress site without extensive customization, you can white-label or brand the most essential and visible aspects of the WordPress Admin interface without having to resort to custom Admin themes or other coding hacks.</p>\n<p>You can take white-labeling one step further and also customize certain aspects of the WordPress Admin through menu tools and role editors to simplify its use and keep your clients from dangerous options such as updates or code editors.</p>\n<p>If you are building a child theme or custom plugin for your site and prefer to implement as much admin customization as you can via functions, see our <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/how-to-white-label-the-wordpress-admin/" target="_blank">Dev Tutorial for How to White Label the WordPress Admin</a></p>\n<h3>Disabling Layers Footer Icon</h3>\n<p>Layers will add a small Layers badge to the footer of your site by default which you can disable from the Customizer under the Footer Styling panel. Of course, you get extra-awesome points for leaving it on and helping spread the word about the Layers framework.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2039" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/support-layers.jpg" alt="support-layers" width="288" height="86" /></p>\n<h3>Adding Your Own Credit &amp; Copyright Text</h3>\n<p>The text footer of Layers contains a default copyright that you may customize from the Customizer under the Footer Styling panel. This field also accepts basic HTML, so adding an icon or logo of your own is as simple as grabbing the file url to your image in the Media Library, and linking it from a standard <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag.</p>\n<p>See <a class="question-title" href="http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-add-images-to-the-footer/" rel="bookmark">How to Add Images to the Footer Copyright area</a> for a detailed tutorial on adding images in the Layers footer.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2040" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/copyrighttext.jpg" alt="copyrighttext" width="288" height="86" /></p>\n<h3>Replacing WordPress Login and Admin Logos</h3>\n<p>If your clients or staff are logging in through the traditional WordPress admin page, they will be greeted by a WordPress logo that links to the site main page. This can be confusing for less-savvy users, especially if they click that logo and are whisked away from the login without knowing quite what happened.</p>\n<p><img class="size-full wp-image-2041 alignright" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/wp-login.jpg" alt="wp-login" width="344" height="469" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/wp-login-220x300.jpg 220w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/wp-login.jpg 344w" sizes="(max-width: 344px) 100vw, 344px" /></p>\n<p>You can change this logo with custom functions in a child theme, or using a plugin such as <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/ag-custom-admin/" target="_blank">AG Custom Admin</a>. This free plugin is an essential part of any site you build and plan to maintain for your clients.</p>\n<p>It allows you to customize all the branded aspects of the WordPress admin, including logos and admin footer text.</p>\n<p>By giving your clients the role of Editor (rather than Administrator), you can also  lock down important menu links and add new ones, which we will expand on in a bit.</p>\n<p>With AG Custom Admin enabled, click on Tools AG Custom Admin to access the Admin Bar and Login Page tabs for logo and color customization. Be careful with the first three options to disable the admin bar or admin bar customizations.</p>\n<p>If you want your clients to be able to create and edit Layers pages, you should allow them to retain access to the admin bar while viewing the front-end so they can easily click into the Customizer from any page.</p>\n<h3>Change WordPress Admin Bar</h3>\n<p>Once logged in, your client is going to see the WordPress Dashboard with the default Howdy! greeting and a WordPress branded admin bar. If you&#8217;ve decided to go the easy route with AG Custom Admin, you can change the Admin branding options on the Admin tab:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload your logo to the WordPress Media Library</li>\n<li>Grab the File Url from the right side of the Image details screen once it is uploaded</li>\n<li>In the AG Custom Admin options, paste the URL into the Change Admin Bar Logo field. You may also simply hide the icon by checking the Hide WordPress Logo option below this.</li>\n<li>Scroll to the bottom to find the Change Howdy text and Change Logout Text to customize these messages.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Change Admin Colors</h3>\n<p>The AG Custom Admin plugin  offers a Colorizer tab for changing the admin menu and admin bar colors.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2043" src="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/custom-admin.jpg" alt="custom-admin" width="852" height="608" srcset="http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/custom-admin-300x214.jpg 300w, http://www.layerswp.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/custom-admin.jpg 852w" sizes="(max-width: 852px) 100vw, 852px" /></p>\n<p>To do this on your own with a child theme, you would need to write a custom admin.css file, then enqueue it normally from your Child Theme functions:</p><pre class="crayon-plain-tag">function layers_child_admin_css() {\n    wp_enqueue_style( \n      ''admin_css'', \n      get_stylesheet_directory_uri() . ''/assets/css/admin.css'' );\n}\n\nadd_action(''admin_enqueue_scripts'', ''layers_child_admin_css'' );</pre><p>You can also write the CSS directly to the function and have it output in the admin head:</p><pre class="crayon-plain-tag">function my_custom_admin_style() { \n   echo ''&lt;style&gt; body, td, textarea, input, select { \n      font-family: "Lucida Grande"; \n      font-size: 12px; \n   } &lt;/style&gt;''; \n}\n\nadd_action(''admin_head'', ''my_custom_admin_style'');</pre><p>For a detailed walkthrough on building admin CSS, see <a href="http://code.tutsplus.com/articles/customizing-the-wordpress-admin-adding-styling--wp-33530" target="_blank">Customizing the WordPress Admin by our friends at Tuts+</a></p>\n<h3>Change the WordPress Admin Footer</h3>\n<p>At the bottom of every page in the WordPress admin you will find a Thank You for Creating with WordPress! message and a version number. If your clients don&#8217;t know or care that you are using WordPress for the site, or if you just want more control over outgoing links and branding, you can change or remove this easily.</p>\n<p>From AG Custom Admin options, head into the Admin Footer tab where you can find the Change Footer Text and Change Footer Version fields, or options to hide them.</p>\n<h3>Customizing the Admin Dashboard</h3>\n<p>Now that you have customized the visual aspects of the WordPress Admin, you can start thinking about the content you want your clients and site users to see. The WordPress Dashboard is the first content a logged in user sees, and while anyone can customize their own view via the Screen Options menu, you may need to remove existing metaboxes, or add some new ones to deliver the best user experience for your client.</p>\n<p>The next tab in your AG Custom Admin options is the Admin Dashboard tab. Here you can easily add content and HTML to the Dashboard header, and disable any default widgets. What this does not do is allow you to turn off widgets added through other plugins or by Layers. To do that, you will need to reference the plugin options or add a custom function to a child theme.</p>\n<h3>Customizing the Admin Menu &amp; Client Access</h3>\n<p>In most cases where you are maintaining your client websites, it is a good idea to restrict access to certain admin areas, both for the safety of the site overall, and simply to reduce confusion for clients unfamiliar with the WordPress Admin. Examples might be hiding links to plugin settings (such as AG Custom Admin), the Appearance &gt; Editor screen or Layers Marketplace.</p>\n<p>Customizing the Admin menu is a task truly best left to a plugin. Both AG Custom Admin and specialized plugins like <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/admin-menu-editor/" target="_blank">Admin Menu Editor</a> are actively developed and updated, and can get the job done for free.</p>\n<p>If using AG Custom Admin, you may edit all admin menu labels and access rights from the Admin Menu tab of the settings. Checking a menu item will remove it from access for Editors, so this plugin depends on you ensuring your clients User Role is set to Editor and not Administrator.</p>\n<p>If your client is the type that likes to see the Admin role on their account, but is too dangerous to be left with full rights, you can use another very handy free plugin called <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/members/" target="_blank">Members</a>, written by WordPress Core developer Justin Tadlock. This is the best approach if you choose to move forward with using the Admin Menu Editor plugin instead, and here&#8217;s why.</p>\n<h4>Creating a Super User and Editing Client Privileges</h4>\n<ol>\n<li>With the Members plugin active, go to Users &gt; Roles.</li>\n<li>Click Add New to add a new role called &#8220;Super-Admin.&#8221;</li>\n<li>Check the boxes on all the capabilities and Save</li>\n<li>Now back out to the main Users list and edit yourself. Select the new Super Admin role from the Role drop-down and Save.</li>\n<li>Return to the Users &gt; Roles page and edit Administrator. Here is where you can remove some capabilities from this role. Common capabilities you want to Deny would be:\n<ul>\n<li>General: edit_roles: deny ability to change your custom roles</li>\n<li>Appearance: switch_themes: deny ability to switch themes from your set active theme.</li>\n<li>Plugins: activate_plugins: deny ability to install new plugins that may potentially break the site.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The important step here is that your clients are assigned the Admin role while you have Super Admin with all capabilities. When using Admin Menu Editor for example, you can now turn off specific Admin Menu items or sub-links by setting them to the Super Admin role.</p>\n<p>This is useful for hiding menu links such as Marketplace, Tools, Editor and other plugin items you might have such as Performance or SEO. You can also hide the entire Layers menu from your clients if you wish.</p>\n<p>With both AG Custom Admin and Admin Menu Editor, you may also customize menu icons and labels and rearrange them with drag and drop if needed.</p>\n<h3>Adding Links To the Admin Menu</h3>\n<p>Easily add new links or entire Admin Menus from the Admin Menu tab of AG Custom Admin (bottom of page) or using the Add Menu button in the Admin Menu Editor options. This allows you to build helpful menus that link to most-used admin pages or offsite resources.</p>\n<h3>Creating Custom Onboarding Pages</h3>\n<p>If you have developed a Layers Child Theme for your client project or are thinking about using one instead of plugins, you can add a custom onboarding function that displays the first time your client logs in with your child theme active, or which they can revisit from a custom menu option.</p>\n<p>We wrote a full developer article on how to do this in a Layers Child Theme as part of the Child Theme Author Guide: <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/how-to-add-help-pages-onboarding-to-layers-themes-or-extensions/">How to Add Help Pages &amp; Onboarding to Layers Themes or Extensions</a></p>\n<h3>Changing Text in Layers</h3>\n<p>In extreme cases where you need to remove Layers branding, you must use a translation tool to remove each instance of &#8220;Layers.&#8221; See our <a href="http://docs.layerswp.com/doc/how-to-translate-or-localize-layers/" target="_blank">guide on translating Layers </a>for plugin suggestions and tips.</p>\n<p>Know of some other great plugins or ways to customize the WordPress Admin that we didn&#8217;t cover here? Tell us in the comments!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/">Easy WordPress White-labeling For Your Clients</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/easy-wordpress-white-labeling-for-your-clients/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"Refreshing a best seller with Concept Living, a WordPress Furniture Theme";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 10:30:55 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2016";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:417:"<p>We’re on a mission to bring some of our finest Obox Themes into the Layers fold. Step 1 in that process is Concept Living.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/">Refreshing a best seller with Concept Living, a WordPress Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Marc Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2297:"<p>Today we’re happy to launch <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living%20Launch%20Post">Concept Living</a>, a WordPress furniture theme for furniture retailers. Originally called Store and built on Obox Themes technology, we decided that Layers offered a perfect opportunity to modernize it.</p>\n<p>During Obox Themes’ 7 year existence we have created well over 100 themes, some for WordPress, some for Tumblr, some for Posterous… but mostly WordPress.</p>\n<p>Of those themes there have been some stand out performers, including <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/gigawatt-wordpress-video-theme/492944?ref=obox">Gigawatt</a>, <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/retail-therapy-multipurpose-ecommerce-theme/5636873?ref=obox">Retail Therapy</a>, <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/the-writer-premium-wordpress-blogging-theme/5908925?ref=obox">The Writer</a> etc. So when we sat down to decide what our next Layers theme was going to be we realized that the answer may be staring us in the face &#8211; why not take our best Obox Themes and give them a fresh coat of paint and a brand new foundation?</p>\n<p>New features include a mobile first design, multiple header layouts, StoreKit integration, Layers page building functionality and much more.</p>\n<p>Check out the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/full_screen_preview/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living%20Launch%20Post">demo</a> or find out more by visiting <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/concept-living-layers-woocommerce-theme/5388303?ref=obox&amp;utm_source=blog.layers&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=Blog%3A%20Concept%20Living%20Launch%20Post">Concept Living</a> on Themeforest.</p>\n<p>We look forward to bringing you much more of our finest work in the near future.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/">Refreshing a best seller with Concept Living, a WordPress Furniture Theme</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/announcing-concept-living-a-wordpress-furniture-theme/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"Introducing Layers Pro, the best extension we’ve ever made";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 18 Nov 2015 08:45:45 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"News";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Layers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14:"layers updates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://www.layerswp.com/?p=2001";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:380:"<p>Unlock customizability in the Layers framework with extended control over design and layout settings.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/">Introducing Layers Pro, the best extension we’ve ever made</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Marc Perel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4851:"<p>The number one request we get from Layers users is the ability to do more. More customizability, more colors, more control.</p>\n<p>When we set about building Layers we wanted to focus on the most important needs of a website and then work our way up from there. Our number one focus was to avoid throwing the kitchen sink at you.</p>\n<p>The strategy has worked well, with tons of great sites being built, but as people have conquered the logic of page building so they have reached a point where more control is needed.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> bridges the gap between a solid site and being really creative.</p>\n<h3><b>What does Layers Pro give me?</b></h3>\n<p>There are a number of features that Layers Pro enables when you install the extension on your site:</p>\n<h4><b>Header Styling</b></h4>\n<p>Finally you can “make the logo bigger” with flexible logo size options, and if our small, medium, large and massive  presets aren’t perfect for you then we’ve included ‘custom’ resizing too.</p>\n<p>Height adjustment and menu spacing has been included for that pixel perfect header layout.</p>\n<p>Another big request was the ability to customize your site menus, which is now possible with colors, spacing, shadows and text-transforming.</p>\n<h4><b>Blog Controls</b></h4>\n<p>From day one you can determine exactly which elements you’d like to display on your list and post pages:</p>\n<p><strong>These include the toggling of:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Featured Images</li>\n<li>Post Dates</li>\n<li>Post Categories</li>\n<li>Post Tags</li>\n<li>Post Author</li>\n<li>Post Excerpt lengths and the “Read More” button text can be changed too.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4><b>More Color Options</b></h4>\n<p>You requested deeper color customization, so we went to town…</p>\n<p>Color options are now split into contextual areas which cuts out the need to click in and out of accordions to get to the place you want. It’s a massive UX improvement that’s performed well in testing.</p>\n<p>Button customization is also vastly improved with the addition of border color, thickness and radius. You can determine button styling on both light and dark backgrounds.</p>\n<p>Menu coloring, blog post coloring, widgets and more have been included in <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a>.</p>\n<p>We will constantly be adding new color customization parameters to Layers Pro so that you have even more control over your site without requiring knowledge of code.</p>\n<h4><b>Tweak the Footer</b></h4>\n<p>New footer options have been added with the inclusion of a new height setting and color customization.</p>\n<h4><b>4 New Widgets and a great update to the Content Widget</b></h4>\n<p>A major part of <a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Layers Pro</a> is the inclusion of new widgets which allow for different ways to display content:</p>\n<p>The <strong>Tab</strong> and <strong>Accordion</strong> widgets enable you to present multiple pages or paragraphs of content in one place. Use it for sequential information such as steps or product tours, or group information that relates to each other.</p>\n<p>We’ve included a new <strong>Post Carousel</strong> widget which outputs your latest blog posts and can slide via controls or automatically with a timer of your choice.</p>\n<p>A much needed <strong>Call to Action</strong> widget is also available from today which you can use to direct user to your products, important blog posts or contact page with multiple buttons under a big header, you no longer have to use the Slider Widget. With the ability to include multiple buttons you can invite them to try your product or read more about it. The choice is yours.</p>\n<p>The most powerful widget, the Content Widget, has also received a subtle but important update which now allows you to add custom class name to individual columns. This will give CSS developers much more flexibility when customizing client or personal websites.</p>\n<h4><b>This is just the start</b></h4>\n<p>We want to ensure that Layers Pro takes the free version of Layers and turns it up to 11. The features we’ve announced today are just the first step in what we hope will be a long update cycle with more features added every month. So if you have any special requests let us know!</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.layerswp.com/layers-pro/">Find out more about Layers Pro</a> or go to directly to CodeCanyon and <a href="http://codecanyon.net/item/layers-pro-extended-customization-for-layers/11225042?ref=obox">purchase it</a> right away.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/">Introducing Layers Pro, the best extension we’ve ever made</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.layerswp.com">Layers</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"http://www.layerswp.com/2015/11/introducing-layers-pro-best-extension-weve-ever-made/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/